collections.name: DOGE of Venice
collections.description:
The Doge of Venice, as the emblem of a storied republic famed for its wealth and sophisticated trade, represents a legacy of innovation and cultural influence. In many ways, the modern world of cryptocurrency and NFTs mirrors that same spirit of forward-thinking—a realm where heritage meets cutting-edge technology.

Imagine a digital portrait of the Doge, enshrined on the blockchain as an NFT, serving as both a collectible work of art and a testament to enduring tradition. Just as the Doge once balanced the scales of commerce, art, and governance, this digital incarnation bridges centuries, inviting today’s collectors and enthusiasts to engage with history in a vibrant, decentralized format.

By representing the Doge of Venice on the blockchain, we not only preserve a piece of our cultural heritage but also celebrate the transformative power of modern technology—a fitting homage to a leader who once defined the pulse of a thriving empire.

collections.name: infinity
collections.description:
Silver Infinity – The Eternity of Freedom
In the endless blackness of the night, a shadow emerged. But this was not darkness—it was a being born of light, a creature woven from silver, moving with the spirit of the wind. Silver Infinity.

It was more than just a horse; it was the embodiment of freedom, courage, and the infinite dance of the soul. Its flowing mane and tail rose like silk waves into the sky, shining like a star carrying its own light within the darkness. Those who gazed upon it found different meanings: some saw an escape from past sorrows, others saw a fearless leap into the future, and some perceived inner transformation and rebirth...

Silver Infinity kept running—its journey had no end, for eternity was in its very nature.

collections.name: Broken Estates: Origin District
collections.description:
Broken Estates is a unique collection of abstract architectural drawings inspired by Theo van Doesburg’s modernist vision. Each artwork represents a house within a district, contributing to a growing digital metropolis where every structure has a unique address.

Embracing geometric abstraction and minimalist design, each house forms diverse, visually engaging districts when combined. As collectors acquire multiple houses, they shape evolving neighborhoods, building their own sections of the city.

More than just digital art, Broken Estates merges architecture and blockchain technology, offering a new way to experience and collect visionary cityscapes. Each district will be released as a new collection, gradually expanding the metropolis and forming an intricate, interconnected urban landscape. This is just the beginning—many more collections are on the horizon, each pushing the boundaries of digital architecture and artistic exploration.

collections.name: belmontag
collections.description:
This is the online gallery of award winning german artist and writer Holger Montag. He is famous for the quality and the large bandwith in his work: Figurative and abstract painter, ink draftsman, author of romancies and childrens books, illustrator, workshop teacher, content creator, sometimes actor, editor and much more. 

The painting techniques also show a wide range. Holger Montag paints with sponges, toothbrushes, credit cards, his hands - occasionally also with painting implements like brushes or ink pens. The materials he uses include lino, lacquer and varnish as well as acrylic paint, chalk, ash, wood, cement, concrete and crumbling plaster.

All works on this page are made by himself and most of the original artworks are also available at belmontag.de, the official website of Holger Montag. Please feel free for asking if you are interested in details about the works: kunst@belmontag.de

collections.name: Botanical Art: Gardenia Jasminoides
collections.description:
Immerse yourself in the delicate beauty of Gardenia Jasminoides, a botanical NFT collection by Heni, a passionate botanical artist from Bali, Indonesia. Each artwork in this collection captures the timeless elegance of gardenia flowers, meticulously crafted with a blend of hand-drawn techniques and digital enhancements.

Known for their exquisite white petals and intoxicating fragrance, gardenias symbolize purity, love, and renewal. Through this collection, Heni brings the enchanting charm of these blooms into the digital world, offering art collectors and nature lovers a unique and timeless floral masterpiece.

Own a piece of botanical elegance and let the beauty of Gardenia Jasminoides blossom in your collection. 🌿✨

collections.name: The Father is Waiting.
collections.description: In the cold breath of the cathedral, beneath shattered saints and stained glass, the Templarhood gathers. Draped in black and white, without faces, without name, they are bound by a vow older than kings. Silence reigns. No prayer is spoken aloud. They wait, still as statues, for the voice that does not speak in words. The Father does not arrive. He does not descend. He simply waits. And in that waiting, judgment begins.

collections.name: Oathbound
collections.description: If love is fated to end, does that make it any less true? Inspired by the timeless tragedy of Shakespeare’s star-crossed lovers, “Oathbound” explores love at the edges—of cultures, of styles, of life and death itself. In each of these 60 unique one-of-one pieces, lovers meet across impossible borders: masks and flesh, East and West, race and tradition. Bound by love, yet divided by history and styles, they exist in the in-between, where identity is both a vow and an act of defiance. Designed and brought to life through Orangehare’s in-house production process, “Oathbound” asks: is love’s power in its endurance, or in its fleeting, unbreakable promise?

collections.name: Light in the Dark: Eternal Illumination in a Digital World
collections.description:
At first glance, this collection plays with contrasts—light and shadow, clarity and mystery. But look closer, and a deeper truth emerges: this is not conflict, but harmony. "Light in the Dark" is a collection of unique NFTs where chiaroscuro meets introspection. Shadows do not obscure—they reveal, inviting reflection on the nature of illumination, both external and internal.

Each portrait captures a moment where light and darkness coexist, creating a sense of stillness. These half-veiled faces do not just look at you—they ask silent questions. What do we truly see in the absence of light? What truths lie within the shadows? True awareness is found not in extremes, but in the space between.

With Sanskrit-inspired titles—"refuge of life","silent grace","the first rays of dawn"—this collection reflects reverence for life, wisdom, and the hidden depths of being. More than art, these NFTs are timeless meditations, unchanging in a transient world.

Are you ready to find light in the dark?
